        "bioghist": [
            {
                "id": "aspace_f0b35b0a1de677c0ff7c139869fbef40",
                "head": {
                    "value": "Biographical Note"
                },
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "Librettist, lyricist, and writer Michael Colby (1951- ) has written musicals including \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eCharlotte Sweet,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eTales of Tinseltown,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eNorth Atlantic,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eSlay it with Music,\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eLudlow Ladd\u003c/span\u003e. Colby's grandparents, Ben and Mary Bodne, purchased the Algonquin Hotel in 1946. Colby's book \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003e The Algonquin Kid: Adventures Growing Up at New York's Legendary Hotel \u003c/span\u003e chronicles his childhood and early adulthood living in the hotel with his grandparents. They eventually sold the hotel in 1987."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
